Found it! The base Tool interface is:
```typescript
export interface Tool<TParameters extends TSchema = TSchema> {
    name: string;
    description: string;
    parameters: TParameters;
}
```

And AgentTool extends it and adds:
- label: string
- execute: (toolCallId, params, signal?, onUpdate?) => Promise<AgentToolResult>

So `description` must be a string, not a method. The duplicate key warning is because I have both `description: string` and `async description()` method in the same object literal. The method will overwrite the string.

Looking at the glob tool more carefully, I see it has:
```typescript
{
    description: "string value",
    // ...
    async description(params) { ... }
}
```

This is JavaScript shorthand - `description` is the string, and `description(params)` is a method. But wait, that doesn't work because they have the same key. Let me re-check glob:

